                  <accMat>
                     <p>On fol. <locus>15</locus> there is an AM-slip pasted in: <q xml:lang="is">NB
                           Sigurdr Hringr atti <lb/> Alfhilldi dottur Gand<lb rend="hyphenated"/>alfs, Alfgeirs sonar. <lb/> Alfssonar, Raumssonar, <lb/> Nors sonar.
                           <lb/> brædur k<unclear reason="damage">onu</unclear> hans <lb/> voru
                           þesser Gandalfs <lb/> synir.</q></p>
                     <p>Fol. <locus>16</locus> has: <q xml:lang="la">
                           <hi rend="underline">Fenhring</hi> hodie <hi rend="underline">Ask<lb rend="hyphenated"/>óre</hi> vocant; Bergis <lb/> vicina est.
                              Confundun<lb rend="hyphenated"/>tur antem heic diver<lb rend="hyphenated"/>si Starcadi; Etenim <lb/> hicce non est ille, de
                           <lb/> qvo Hrolfi Gotricii <lb/> vita agit, qvi vika<lb/>rum Suspendit.
                           Sed <lb/> antiqvitas omnia in <lb/> unu<ex>m</ex> congestit.</q>
                     </p>
                     <p>The former cover of the first item (fols <locus>1r-25v</locus>), containing
                        Danish historical and geographical notes, is now made into the first quire of the
                        manuscript. On this <name type="person" key="ArnMag001">Árni
                           Magnússon</name> wrote: <q xml:lang="la">Nornagestz þattr <lb/> ex
                           membranâ Regia. <lb/> Est qvasi Melagri <lb/> fabula.</q> On two extra
                        added leaves he states: <q xml:lang="la">Ur Nornagestz þætti. <lb/> Variæ
                           lectiones Codicis Regii, <lb/> apatatæ ad Apographum meum Hi<lb rend="hyphenated"/>storiæ Olavi Tryggvonii ex Co<lb rend="hyphenated"/>dice Flateyensi, qvod exaratum <lb/> est manu Domini Jonæ Erlendii.</q>
                     </p>
